From winter semester 2016/17 the studies are counted according � 22 UHSBV. This means that studies have to be rounded to whole numbers and there may be discrepancies between the total and the added detailed results.

In the surveys based on the Ordinance on University and Higher Education Statistics and Educational Documentation - UHSBV. Federal Law Gazette II No. 216/2019. gender is also surveyed for diverse and all other gender that are neither male nor female (third sex). Due to the small number of cases of persons with the third sex. they are assigned to the binary forms male or female by imputation for data protection reasons in STATcube.
